<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="580" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="96.[2069,2663,2512,2937]" pageId="96" pageNumber="580">
Several subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[2369,2512,2627,2660]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Ardops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="96" pageNumber="580" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nichollsi">A. nichollsi</taxonomicName>
have been described and are distributed in 13 Lesser Antilles islands; subspecies annectens named by G. S. Miller, Jr. in 1913 (from 
<collectingCountry name="Guadeloupe" pageId="96" pageNumber="580">Guadeloupe</collectingCountry>
and Marie-Galante) was recently synonymized with montserratensis. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
